<paragraph blockId="16.[168,775,993,1451]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
cence: a loose pubescence panicle, to 
<quantity box="[587,655,993,1017]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" unit="cm" value="15.0">15 cm</quantity>
long, with multiflorous lanceolate spikelets. Glumes 
<quantity box="[651,774,1026,1050]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="16.0">16–30 mm</quantity>
long, outgrowing flower sets. Spikelets with 5–10 flow- ers; lemma 
<quantity box="[297,407,1093,1117]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–4 mm</quantity>
long, ovate-lanceolate, with bifid apex. Central twisted awn brown or colorless, 
<quantity box="[668,775,1126,1150]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" unit="cm" value="19.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="15.0">15–23 cm</quantity>
long, inserted at bifurcation point of lemma. Fruit: an obovate caryopsis.
</paragraph>
