<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[168,775,993,1451]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,336,1226,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">Comments.</emphasis>
This is a frequent species in the study area. It grows in shallow to moderately deep soils on slopes, in grasslands, and around the pond. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hack. &amp; Arechav." authorityName="Hack. &amp; Arechav." box="[198,602,1327,1351]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Danthonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cirrata">
<emphasis box="[198,394,1327,1351]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">Danthonia cirrata</emphasis>
Hack. &amp; Arechav.
</taxonomicName>
, which also has been found in the Paititi Reserve, but the lemma of the latter species has the lateral lobes longer than the undivided part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
